Sorting
Bubble Sort: It repeatedly compares adjacent element and swaps them if out of order.Each passes a "bubble" the biggest/largest
unsorted element to its correct order position. Usually the time complexity is O(n2) worst/average.O(n) best(optimized) Space O(1).


Merge Sort: (Divide and Conquer) . It divides the array in half recursively, sorts each half and then merges them. It is a classic divide and conquer algorithm.
Time complexity: O(nlogn) Always
Space: O(n)

